description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Bank Midwife, you&#39;ll work at the heart of our community here in Surrey atEpsom and St Helier. Caring for all pregnant, labouring and postnatal women. As you provide support, guidance and care for mother, baby and family, we’ll support you through flexible shifts that fit around your lifestyle. Our friendly community-minded hospitals are easily accessible from London and the surrounding area and offer the chance to really belong not just to a team, but to a family.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide maternity care for around 5,000 mothers and their babies every year. Our maternity services are provided at both the Epsom and St Helier hospitals. Both hospitals have inpatient antenatal (during pregnancy) and postnatal (after the birth) facilities along with midwifery-led birth centre and obstetric-led labour wards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer great rates, access to the NHS pension, free mandatory training and the support of a professional and friendly team from the moment you register with us, to your first shift and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To join, you must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Currently be registered with the NMC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Be eligible to work in the UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Pass an enhanced DBS check&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Must have a minimum of 6 months recentrelevant experience**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud to be an accredited Baby Friendly maternity unit, recognising our high standards in encouraging and supporting new mums to bond with their babies and make the best personal choice in how to feed their new-born&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply with your CV now to join the StaffBank team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bank Partners are a leading provider of independent staffing bank management and outsourced staffing services providing workers to some of the largest trusts in the NHS. We have over 20 years experience in managing hospital banks and we take pride in the knowledge that we provide a high quality service to the trusts we represent, supplying them with workers across multiple specialism’s including Doctors, Nurses and Allied Health Professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
